reviews.text: The pork needed flavor, the potato salad needed more mustard or spice, the coleslaw needed more vinegar.  The fries were good. It's okay but could be better.

Felt really old school southern vibe. Honestly I really appreciate the interior bc if you have been in GA for any good length of time you‚Äôll know that a lot has changed.

The food was pretty good, I gotta come back and try the smoked chicken salad sandwich. I wanna try the baked beans and other sides.
My favorite BBQ spot. Delicious food and cozy atmosphere

Our BBQ pork, black eyed peas, collard greens, and cold slaw were delicious! The pork was extremely lean and the flavor amazing. Combining the welcoming atmosphere created by the efficient and smiling staff, even though we placed our order to go, with the perfectly seasoned sides made for a perfect ending to our day after driving from out of state.

For my family I ordered two 3-bone rib plates and a small brisket sandwich. All of the food was really good! The ribs had a good portion of meat on them. The small brisket sandwich also had a good portion of meat.
Multiple workers spoke and acknowledged me, which made me feel welcomed. I will return to support this family owned local restaurant.

editorial_summary.overview: Branch of a local chain offering Southern-style BBQ meats & sides for casual dine-in or takeout.

detailedReviews.text: Worst BBQ I‚Äôve ever had. My colleague suggested this place for lunch, and I‚Äôll never return. I had the 1/4 chicken, Mac and cheese, and baked beans‚Ä¶everything was nasty. Corn bread was okay. I liked the corn kernels inside‚Ä¶nice touch.

detailedReviews.author: Fred Edwards
detailedReviews.text:
I had the 3 Rib plate with two sides for $24 with tip. The Ribs were VERY small and had no flavor. There was zero seasoning and the sauce didn't help. The Mac and Cheese was bland with no seasoning. The Fried Okra was obviously frozen, had no seasoning and was fried too long.

I was so underwhelmed by the food quality.

It was lunch time and there was only a few tables occupied. One guy behind the counter and one server for the entire restaurant.

detailedReviews.author: GaTech Grad
detailedReviews.text: Glenn & the gang provide a fun, delicious, and speedy food experience.  Fried okra and sweet tea.  Brisket and ribs.  Food delivered to your table sometimes before you sit down.  I like sitting in the Elvis Section.  Our kid likes the grilled cheese and baked beans. Count the quilts and the pigs.

detailedReviews.author: Kelsey May
detailedReviews.text: This place is amazing. When you walk in there are photos on the wall showcasing various veterans. It was very nice to see appreciation of American heros. They offer a military discount as well. The staff was awesome, and the blonde guy there even told me a few stories behind some of the photos. The food was amazing, the best barbecue I‚Äôve had outside of Tennessee. We went about an hour before they closed and the staff was nice enough to hook me up with cheddar biscuits that were leftover.

detailedReviews.author: Steve Bailey
detailedReviews.text: Only recently discovered this place. What a great alternative to a traditional meat and two! The vegetables were really good. Black eye peas seemed fresh, great old style Brunswick stew, fried okra, green beans (wide like pole beans!) were great and good lima beans. Next time I'll get the chopped pork unsalted. Friendly staff! If you're in the area it's a must try!

detailedReviews.author: Patty Brown

detailedReviews.text:
Food has always been good over the many years I have eaten at Slopes,  but the last couple years since it has become McDaniel‚Äôs QN2 it has only gotten better!
Our congenial host, Glenn, addresses many of his dedicated customers by name and is always very welcoming to all.
The food is always perfectly prepared and McDaniel‚Äôs QN2 is a definite Neighborhood Gem in Sandy Springs.

detailedReviews.author: Cassandra Gulia
detailedReviews.text: They have the best fall-off-the-bone baby back ribs!! The house BBQ sauces are also phenomenal. A really solid place for bbq in atlanta.

detailedReviews.author: B. A. Brooks
detailedReviews.text: My son and I tried  their food for the first time today and we really enjoyed the wings, they were well done, not salty or greasy. The okra was cooked to perfection, the potato salad was tasty and the wing sauce had just the right amount of heat. I appreciated the patience the staff took with us while we ordered our food. We will definitely return!!!

detailedReviews.author: Jason Timms
detailedReviews.text: I've eaten here two or three times and enjoyed it every single time. Love their pulled pork sandwiches and baked beans

detailedReviews.author: M Bledsoe
detailedReviews.text: The more I think about it (and the hungrier I get before I can have a big supper) the grumpier I get about this very disappointing lunch. The salmon was overcooked and very dry, to the point that it was hard to eat, and almost flavorless.  Could not finish it. Fried okra had no flavor at all and was very tough. Could not finish that either. I am hungry.

detailedReviews.author: Andrea Ratowsky Brenner
detailedReviews.text: Such a lovely atmosphere with such attentive and great staff. We came for a family reunion and everyone was entertained. Especially the kids loved the foozeball table and couch.

detailedReviews.author: Cara Mills
detailedReviews.text: So reliably good.  All the things.  Family owned local business- SUPPORT!

detailedReviews.author: Marquetta Rattler
detailedReviews.text: Food was pretty good. Great atmosphere very welcoming and friendly. Okra was the best and fresh cut tomatoes.

detailedReviews.author: Keith Brown
detailedReviews.text: You wish the McDaniel family were your next door neighbor.  Best people in the world.  Great bbq!

detailedReviews.author: Angela Leslie
detailedReviews.text: I ordered the brisket sandwich with fried okra and coleslaw.   Unfortunately, everything lacked flavor.  I am honestly confused as to why the overall rating is so high.  The bbq sauce was watery and lacked flavor as well.  The meal was just mehhhh.

detailedReviews.author: Randy Stuart
detailedReviews.text:
I used to come here years ago when this was called Slopes to have lunch with my father. I loved the cheese biscuits and the pork rinds. He's gone but his car tag is on the wall.
I was nervous at first when i saw the name change but I found out it is still the same old restaurant that I knew. I like the ribs, they are reasonably priced and good with baked beans and fries.
Regrettably i can't come as often as I used to but I will try in the future.

detailedReviews.author: Bill Tush
detailedReviews.text: Always friendly and always good. Loved the squash casserole. Hear it‚Äôs homemade, my compliments to the chef.

detailedReviews.author: Natasha G
detailedReviews.text: This place was previously named slopes and that‚Äôs how I found it since I love the slopes Roswell location. The owner is super friendly and the brisket I think is even better than the Roswell Slopes and the best BBQ in town. The mega brisket sandwich with coleslaw is the way to go. I had baked beans and coleslaw husband. The kids had chicken sandwiches with tater tots and Mac n cheese. Husband agrees it‚Äôs the best BBQ since we moved here from New Orleans. It‚Äôs nice they have catering as well. Menus attached for reference. I think the price is very reasonable for the quality is amazing.

detailedReviews.author: Cara Polley
detailedReviews.text: Best ribs in the area! Fall off the bone and meaty. Brunswick stew is amazing as well.

detailedReviews.author: Michael Cash
detailedReviews.text: I live in buckhead and ordered through ubereats. I can finally say as a man who has lived in Statesboro, Macon and Eatonton, that I've found my favorite BBQ spot up this way and it competes with some of the best I've ever had. I tried the pulled pork and potato salad and they were great. I was nervous about trying the stew bc bad stew ruins it for me but yalls is also great. Repeat customer here.
